cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.MM, cs.SY, cs.AR 

This paper discusses the implementation of multi-user transmissions in IEEE 802.11ax WLANs, which is a topic related to network protocols and communication technologies. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves mathematical analysis and simulations to study the achievable throughput, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.IT (Information Theory). Additionally, the use of multi-user MIMO and OFDMA transmissions in WLANs is related to multimedia communication and signal processing, which could place the paper in cs.MM (Multimedia). The paper also discusses changes made at the medium access control layer, which is related to system design and control, suggesting that it could belong to cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper proposes new mechanisms to protect large multi-user transmissions from collisions, which could place it in cs.AR (Hardware Architecture).
